  [2]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/net/InetAddress.html#isReachable-int-
  [3]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/net/HttpURLConnection.html
  [4]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/net/HttpURLConnection.html#setRequestMethod-java.lang.String-
  [5]: http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec10.html#sec10.4.6
  [6]: http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec10.html

Instead of using URLConnection use [HttpURLConnection][1] by calling openConnection() on your URL object. 

Then use [getResponseCode()][2] will give you the HTTP response once you&#39;ve read from the connection.

